AETHERMUD CREATOR GUIDE: BUILD (QUICK CREATION SYSTEM)

The build command is the Quick Creation System (QCS) dispatcher. It is
granted by the Staff of Creation, which coding wizards receive on
promotion and must hold in inventory. Admin wizards may also use it.

Files are generated under your realm: /realms/<you>/area/ in the
subdirectories room/, npc/, weap/, and armor/. Most verbs require you
to be standing inside your own realm.

In-game shortcuts:
  build              same as build help (quick summary)
  build help         quick summary from the staff tool
  help build         this full topic (creators only)
  help qcs           short QCS overview that points here

CREATING THINGS

  build create room <direction> <filename>
      Makes a new room file, links it from your current room in the
      given direction, and adds the reverse exit back.
      Example: build create room north guard_post

  build create npc <filename>
      Makes a new NPC file from the QCS template.
      Example: build create npc bandit

  build create weapon <filename>
      Makes a new weapon file.
      Example: build create weapon vibro_knife

  build create armor <filename>
      Makes a new armor file.
      Example: build create armor leather_jacket

MODIFYING THINGS

  build modify here <property> <value>
      Changes a property of the room you are standing in.
      Example: build modify here short A dusty guard post

  build modify <filename> <property> <value>
      Changes a property of a file in your realm area.
      Example: build modify bandit level 5

  Room properties:   short, long, light, indoors
  NPC properties:    name, short, long, level, hp, race, occ, align, mdc
  Weapon properties: name, short, long, wc, type, damage (NdN), mdc (0/1)
  Armor properties:  name, short, long, ac, ar, sdc, mdc, slot

  Files recompile automatically after each modify.

EXITS AND POPULATION

  build add exit <direction> <path>
      Adds an exit from your current room to the given room path.
      Example: build add exit east /realms/you/area/room/armory

  build add <npcfile> to here
      Adds a reset() spawn of the NPC to your current room.
      Example: build add bandit to here

  build add <npcfile> to <roomfile>
      Same, but for a named room file instead of the current room.
      Example: build add bandit to guard_post

OTHER VERBS

  build delete <object>       Removes an object in the room (not living).
  build clone <filename>      Clones a file from your realm area into
                              your inventory (NPCs go to the room).
  build about <file|here>     Summary of a generated file.
  build more <file|here>      Full source listing of a generated file.

Held-staff extras (same tool, own verbs, no build prefix):
  clone <path>                Clone any file by path or realm name.
  purge <object>              Destroy a non-living object in the room.

NOTES

  - QCS requires the Staff of Creation in your inventory. Losing the
    staff disables all build verbs; it returns on login (autoload).
  - Generated files are plain LPC. You can hand-edit them afterward
    with ed and reload with update.
  - Filenames are sanitized to lowercase letters, digits, and
    underscores.
  - help build is a creator/staff topic. Mortals will not see it.

See also: qcs, ed
